<BaseLayout title="Legal | Homelab Fit">
  <section class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1>Copyright, trademark, and source policy</h1>
    <p>Homelab Fit is built to be a third-party compatibility reference, not an official product documentation clone.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-block">
    <h2>Independent status</h2>
    <p>Homelab Fit is independent and is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by Proxmox Server Solutions GmbH, Intel, AMD, Minisforum, Beelink, or other vendors.</p>
    <h2>Trademark policy</h2>
    <p>Product names, service names, and logos belong to their respective owners. This site does not use official product logos as site branding and should not present itself as official support, documentation, or certification.</p>
    <h2>Source policy</h2>
    <p>Indexable pages should cite primary documentation where possible. Community posts and forum discussions can inform real-world symptoms, but should not be copied as page content.</p>
    <h2>Accuracy policy</h2>
    <p>Hardware revisions, firmware, kernels, and Proxmox versions can change behavior. Verify critical storage, networking, and passthrough decisions against your exact hardware before trusting production data to a setup.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
